  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Clean Water Supply to Drought Hit Areas of Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Civil war, drought, and economic instability have led to a recently declared famine in South Sudan, and Uganda where nearly over 5 million people face extreme food shortages in South Sudan and 10 million in Uganda are facing fatal challenges of famine. Serious drought conditions across the region have also led to food crises in Western regions and West Nile, Karamoja subregions and Refuguees .  Women and Girls spend two days waiting for water at the bore hole points, leaving kids home hungry.</narrative>
  </description>
